featured_reviews.review_id:
This place of worship for followers of the Islamic faith. It serves as a gathering place for Muslims to engage in prayer, community activities, and to seek spiritual guidance. Mosques can vary in size and architectural design, reflecting the diverse cultural backgrounds of Muslims worldwide.

Typically, this mosque consists of a prayer hall, often adorned with beautiful calligraphy and geometric designs, where Muslims gather to perform their daily prayers. a niche that indicates the direction of Mecca. A minbar, or pulpit, is also present in the prayer hall, from which the imam, or prayer leader, delivers sermons and guidance to the congregation.

It often have a separate area for ablution, where Muslims perform ritual washing before prayer. This area usually includes facilities for wudu, the ritual washing of the hands, face, and feet.

This mosque are not only place of worship but also serve as centers for education and community outreach. There is also a hifz college( quran studiying Center)running under the mosque

Overall, this mosque play a vital role in the lives of nearby Muslims , providing a space for spiritual growth, community engagement, and a sense of belonging. And promote unity, peace, and the values of Islam, serving as symbols of faith and cultural heritage.
